					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-134166#post-398684</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-134166/scp-050#post-398684</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 27 Feb 2009 15:08:38 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Peri McGovern</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>287380</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This is a nifty idea. But what, exactly, do surveillance cameras record when SCP-050 "cleans?" For example, do papers fly into folders and trash fly into the bin autonomously? Or is it more like a sudden camera glitch happens, and when the picture comes back, viola! The room is sparkling. What happens to the trash in the bin? Does it vanish completely, or does it show up in facility dumpsters? (Or, perhaps as part of its "pranking" behavior, maybe the debris is transplanted to the office of someone "less clever?") A little more explanation of the process would be helpful.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
